<h2>This page does not yet exist.</h2>
<br />
Want to create it?
<br />
<ul>
	@if (!User.Identity.IsAuthenticated)
	{
		<li>If you are an editor or have rights to edit this page, <a asp-action="Login" asp-controller="Account" asp-route-returnUrl="@("/" + ViewData["Title"])">log in</a> to edit the page.</li>
		<li>If you are not an editor, become an <a asp-action="Index" asp-controller="Roles">editor!</a></li>
	}
	@*TODO: nuanced permission checks based on page*@
	@if (User.Identity.IsAuthenticated && ViewData.UserHasPermission(PermissionTo.EditWikiPages))
	{
		<li>Click here to <a asp-controller="Wiki" asp-action="Edit" asp-route-path="@ViewData["Title"]">edit this page</a></li>
		<li>Write the page content, and click Save to create the page.</li>
	}
</ul>

When creating new pages, always ensure that there is some other page that links to the newly created page. Otherwise your page will just become a <a asp-controller="WikiOrphans" asp-action="Index">wiki orphan</a> that will be quickly forgotten.